{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880632547,"sessionID":"ses_2854548aeffeHHpEDliYv7fzzb","part":{"id":"prt_d7abbf8bf001u42spLDWbyWk3o","messageID":"msg_d7abbe21f001Wx9CgBVGQNMfaH","sessionID":"ses_2854548aeffeHHpEDliYv7fzzb","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-94aa5bdf21d14d6b87461934aeeb40cc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-026 ŌĆö K8s/AgentCube Provider\n2: \n3: AR: AR-026 ŌĆö K8s/AgentCube Provider\n4: Module: cmd/cli\n5: Language: Python\n6: Size: M\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Purpose\n11: \n12: Implement K8s/AgentCube provider integration for deploying AI agents as either standard Kubernetes resources (Deployment + Service) or AgentCube Custom Resources (AgentRuntime CR), enabling lifecycle management through CLI commands.\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Requirements\n17: \n18: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider initialization\n19: \n20: The system SHALL construct `KubernetesProvider` with configurable namespace, kubeconfig path, and verbose logging.\n21: \n22: #### Scenario: Default namespace and kubeconfig\n23: \n24: - **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider` is instantiated without arguments\n25: - **WHEN** the constructor runs\n26: - **THEN** `namespace` SHALL default to `\"default\"`, `kubeconfig` SHALL default to `None` (using in-cluster or default kubeconfig), and `verbose` SHALL default to `False`\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: Custom kubeconfig path\n29: \n30: - **GIVEN** a custom kubeconfig file path is provided\n31: - **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider.__init__(kubeconfig=\"/path/to/config\")` runs\n32: - **THEN** the client SHALL load configuration from the specified file via `kubernetes.config.load_kube_config(config_file=kubeconfig)`\n33: \n34: #### Scenario: Namespace auto-creation\n35: \n36: - **GIVEN** the specified namespace does not exist in the cluster\n37: - **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace()` is called\n38: - **THEN** the provider SHALL create the namespace with `kubernetes.client.V1Namespace(metadata=V1ObjectMeta(name=namespace))` and log the creation\n39: \n40: ---\n41: \n42: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider ŌĆö deploy agent\n43: \n44: The system SHALL create or patch a `Deployment` and a `NodePort` `Service` for the agent, returning deployment info.\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: Deployment creation\n47: \n48: - **GIVEN** `deploy_agent(agent_name, image_url, port, entrypoint=None, replicas=1, node_port=None, env_vars=None)` is called\n49: - **WHEN** resources are applied\n50: - **THEN** the provider SHALL:\n51:   - Call `_create_deployment` with sanitized name (DNS-compliant: lowercase, alphanumeric, hyphens, max 63 chars)\n52:   - Call `_create_service` with the same sanitized name\n53:   - Ensure namespace exists via `_ensure_namespace`\n54:   - Return dict with `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `replicas`, `container_port`, `node_port`, `service_url`\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: NodePort assignment\n57: \n58: - **GIVEN** `node_port` is specified in range 30000-32767\n59: - **WHEN** `_create_service` creates the Service\n60: - **THEN** the Service spec SHALL set `type: NodePort` with `nodePort: {node_port}` and `port: {port}` targeting the container port\n61: - **AND** `service_url` SHALL be `http://localhost:{node_port}`\n62: \n63: #### Scenario: Auto NodePort\n64: \n65: - **GIVEN** `node_port` is `None`\n66: - **WHEN** the Service is created\n67: - **THEN** Kubernetes SHALL assign a random NodePort in the valid range\n68: - **AND** the provider SHALL retrieve the assigned port from the Service status\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: Entrypoint override\n71: \n72: - **GIVEN** `entrypoint` is provided\n73: - **WHEN** the Deployment container spec is constructed\n74: - **THEN** `command` SHALL be set to the entrypoint command (parsed as list if string)\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: Environment variables injection\n77: \n78: - **GIVEN** `env_vars` dict is provided\n79: - **WHEN** the Deployment container spec is constructed\n80: - **THEN** each key-value pair SHALL be added as `V1EnvVar(name=key, value=value)`\n81: \n82: #### Scenario: Sanitize name\n83: \n84: - **GIVEN** an agent name with special characters or uppercase\n85: - **WHEN** `_sanitize_name(name)` runs\n86: - **THEN** the result SHALL be: lowercase, replace underscores and spaces with hyphens, strip non-alphanumeric/hyphen chars, truncate to 63 chars, strip leading/trailing hyphens\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider ŌĆö wait for deployment ready\n91: \n92: The system SHALL poll deployment status until all replicas are ready or timeout.\n93: \n94: #### Scenario: Successful rollout\n95: \n96: - **GIVEN** a Deployment with `replicas=3`\n97: - **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready(name, timeout=120)` is called\n98: - **THEN** the provider SHALL poll `read_namespaced_deployment_status` until `status.ready_replicas == replicas` and log progress\n99: - **AND** return when ready within timeout\n100: \n101: #### Scenario: Timeout failure\n102: \n103: - **GIVEN** deployment pods fail to become ready\n104: - **WHEN** `timeout` seconds elapse without all replicas ready\n105: - **THEN** the provider SHALL raise `TimeoutError(f\"Deployment {name} not ready after {timeout} seconds\")`\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider ŌĆö get agent status\n110: \n111: The system SHALL retrieve deployment and service status for the agent.\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: Status retrieval\n114: \n115: - **GIVEN** an agent was deployed via `deploy_agent`\n116: - **WHEN** `get_agent_status(agent_name)` is called\n117: - **THEN** the provider SHALL:\n118:   - Read Deployment status (name, namespace, replicas, ready_replicas, available_replicas)\n119:   - Read Service status (name, port, node_port)\n120:   - Return dict with `status` (`\"running\"` if ready, `\"pending\"` if not ready, `\"not_found\"` if missing)\n121: \n122: #### Scenario: Deployment not found\n123: \n124: - **GIVEN** no Deployment exists for `agent_name`\n125: - **WHEN** `get_agent_status` is called\n126: - **THEN** Kubernetes API SHALL raise `kubernetes.client.exceptions.ApiException` with status 404\n127: - **AND** the provider SHALL catch it and return `{\"status\": \"not_found\"}`\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider ŌĆö delete agent\n132: \n133: The system SHALL delete Deployment and Service resources.\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: Successful deletion\n136: \n137: - **GIVEN** a deployed agent\n138: - **WHEN** `delete_agent(agent_name)` is called\n139: - **THEN** the provider SHALL:\n140:   - Delete Deployment with `delete_namespaced_deployment`\n141:   - Delete Service with `delete_namespaced_service`\n142:   - Return `{\"status\": \"deleted\", \"deployment_name\": ..., \"namespace\": ...}`\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: Ignore 404 on deletion\n145: \n146: - **GIVEN** one or both resources do not exist\n147: - **WHEN** deletion API returns 404\n148: - **THEN** the provider SHALL ignore the error (treat as already deleted) and continue\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ### Requirement: AgentCubeProvider initialization\n153: \n154: The system SHALL construct `AgentCubeProvider` for AgentRuntime CR operations.\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: Default configuration\n157: \n158: - **GIVEN** `AgentCubeProvider` is instantiated\n159: - **WHEN** the constructor runs\n160: - **THEN** `namespace` SHALL default to `\"default\"`, `kubeconfig` to `None`, `verbose` to `False`\n161: \n162: #### Scenario: Custom namespace\n163: \n164: - **GIVEN** a specific namespace is required\n165: - **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider(namespace=\"custom-ns\")` is instantiated\n166: - **THEN** all CR operations SHALL target that namespace\n167: \n168: ---\n169: \n170: ### Requirement: AgentCubeProvider ŌĆö deploy AgentRuntime CR\n171: \n172: The system SHALL create or patch an `AgentRuntime` custom resource in group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`.\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: CR creation\n175: \n176: - **GIVEN** `deploy_agent_runtime(agent_name, image_url, port, entrypoint=None, env_vars=None, workload_manager_url=None, router_url=None, readiness_probe_path=None, readiness_probe_port=None)` is called\n177: - **WHEN** the CR is applied\n178: - **THEN** the provider SHALL:\n179:   - Sanitize agent name via `_sanitize_name`\n180:   - Ensure namespace exists\n181:   - Construct CR body with:\n182:     - `apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n183:     - `kind: AgentRuntime`\n184:     - `metadata.name`, `metadata.namespace`\n185:     - `spec.image`, `spec.port`\n186:     - `spec.command` if entrypoint provided\n187:     - `spec.env` from env_vars (plus `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL` if not in env_vars)\n188:     - `spec.sessionTimeout: \"15m\"`, `spec.maxSessionDuration: \"8h\"`\n189:     - `spec.imagePullSecrets: [{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n190:     - `spec.readinessProbe` if probe path/port provided\n191:   - Create via CustomObjectsApi `create_namespaced_custom_object`\n192:   - Return dict with `cr_name`, `namespace`, `status`\n193: \n194: #### Scenario: Workload Manager URL injection\n195: \n196: - **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url` is provided and not in `env_vars`\n197: - **WHEN** the CR spec is constructed\n198: - **THEN** `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` SHALL be added to `spec.env`\n199: \n200: #### Scenario: Router URL injection\n201: \n202: - **GIVEN** `router_url` is provided and not in `env_vars`\n203: - **WHEN** the CR spec is constructed\n204: - **THEN** `ROUTER_URL` SHALL be added to `spec.env`\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: Readiness probe configuration\n207: \n208: - **GIVEN** `readiness_probe_path` and `readiness_probe_port` are provided\n209: - **WHEN** the CR spec is constructed\n210: - **THEN** `spec.readinessProbe` SHALL include:\n211:   - `httpGet.path: {readiness_probe_path}`\n212:   - `httpGet.port: {readiness_probe_port}`\n213:   - `initialDelaySeconds: 5`\n214:   - `periodSeconds: 10`\n215: \n216: ---\n217: \n218: ### Requirement: AgentCubeProvider ŌĆö get AgentRuntime CR\n219: \n220: The system SHALL retrieve the AgentRuntime CR and its status.\n221: \n222: #### Scenario: CR retrieval\n223: \n224: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime CR exists\n225: - **WHEN** `get_agent_runtime(name, namespace)` is called\n226: - **THEN** the provider SHALL use `get_namespaced_custom_object` with:\n227:   - `group=\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`\n228:   - `version=\"v1alpha1\"`\n229:   - `plural=\"agentruntimes\"`\n230:   - `namespace`, `name`\n231:   - Return the full CR dict or `None` if not found\n232: \n233: #### Scenario: CR not found\n234: \n235: - **GIVEN** no AgentRuntime CR exists for the name\n236: - **WHEN** `get_agent_runtime` is called\n237: - **THEN** the API SHALL raise 404\n238: - **AND** the provider SHALL catch and return `None`\n239: \n240: ---\n241: \n242: ### Requirement: CLI publish ŌĆö provider selection\n243: \n244: The system SHALL route publish operations to `AgentCubeProvider` or `KubernetesProvider` based on `--provider` option.\n245: \n246: #### Scenario: AgentCube provider publish\n247: \n248: - **GIVEN** `--provider agentcube` is specified\n249: - **WHEN** `publish` command runs\n250: - **THEN** `PublishRuntime` SHALL:\n251:   - Validate `metadata.router_url` and `metadata.workload_manager_url` are set (raise `ValueError` if missing)\n252:   - Call `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime`\n253:   - Update metadata with `k8s_deployment: {\"type\": \"AgentRuntime\", \"cr_name\": ..., \"namespace\": ...}`\n254: \n255: #### Scenario: K8s provider publish\n256: \n257: - **GIVEN** `--provider k8s` is specified\n258: - **WHEN** `publish` command runs\n259: - **THEN** `PublishRuntime` SHALL:\n260:   - Call `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent`\n261:   - Call `wait_for_deployment_ready(timeout=120)`\n262:   - Update metadata with `k8s_deployment: {\"type\": \"Deployment\", \"deployment_name\": ..., \"service_name\": ..., \"namespace\": ..., \"node_port\": ...}`\n263:   - Raise `RuntimeError` on readiness timeout, recording error in metadata\n264: \n265: #### Scenario: Provider default\n266: \n267: - **GIVEN** `--provider` is omitted\n268: - **WHEN** `publish` runs\n269: - **THEN** `provider` SHALL default to `\"agentcube\"`\n270: \n271: ---\n272: \n273: ### Requirement: CLI invoke ŌĆö provider-aware endpoint resolution\n274: \n275: The system SHALL resolve invocation endpoint based on deployment type in metadata.\n276: \n277: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime invocation URL\n278: \n279: - **GIVEN** `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`\n280: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs with `provider=\"agentcube\"`\n281: - **THEN** the endpoint SHALL be constructed as:\n282:   - `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n283: \n284: #### Scenario: K8s Deployment invocation URL\n285: \n286: - **GIVEN** `k8s_deployment.type == \"Deployment\"`\n287: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs with `provider=\"k8s\"`\n288: - **THEN** the endpoint SHALL be `http://localhost:{node_port}` from `k8s_deployment.node_port`\n289: \n290: #### Scenario: Direct HTTP invocation for K8s\n291: \n292: - **GIVEN** `provider=\"k8s\"` and endpoint is a direct HTTP URL\n293: - **WHEN** `_direct_http_invocation` runs\n294: - **THEN** the runtime SHALL `POST` JSON payload to the endpoint with custom headers\n295: \n296: ---\n297: \n298: ### Requirement: CLI status ŌĆö provider-aware status retrieval\n299: \n300: The system SHALL retrieve status based on deployment type.\n301: \n302: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime CR status\n303: \n304: - **GIVEN** `provider=\"agentcube\"` and `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`\n305: - **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` runs\n306: - **THEN** status SHALL be:\n307:   - `cr_object[\"status\"][\"status\"]` if present\n308:   - `{\"status\": \"created_no_status\", \"agentEndpoint\": cr[\"status\"][\"agentEndpoint\"]}` if CR exists but status field missing\n309:   - `{\"status\": \"not_found_in_k8s\"}` if CR does not exist\n310: \n311: #### Scenario: K8s Deployment status\n312: \n313: - **GIVEN** `provider=\"k8s\"` and `k8s_deployment.type == \"Deployment\"`\n314: - **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_k8s_status` runs\n315: - **THEN** status SHALL come from `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status`\n316: \n317: #### Scenario: Not published status\n318: \n319: - **GIVEN** `metadata.agent_id` is `None`\n320: - **WHEN** `StatusRuntime.get_status` runs\n321: - **THEN** it SHALL return `{\"status\": \"not_published\"}`\n322: \n323: ---\n324: \n325: ### Requirement: CLI status ŌĆö exit codes\n326: \n327: The system SHALL exit with code 1 for non-ready states.\n328: \n329: #### Scenario: Not published exit\n330: \n331: - **GIVEN** status is `\"not_published\"`\n332: - **WHEN** `status` command prints output\n333: - **THEN** CLI SHALL print guidance message and exit with code `1`\n334: \n335: #### Scenario: Error status exit\n336: \n337: - **GIVEN** status is `\"error\"`\n338: - **WHEN** `status` command completes\n339: - **THEN** CLI SHALL exit with code `1`\n340: \n341: ---\n342: \n343: ### Requirement: Session header consistency\n344: \n345: The system SHALL use consistent session header naming across providers and SDK.\n346: \n347: #### Scenario: Invoke session header\n348: \n349: - **GIVEN** `metadata.session_id` exists\n350: - **WHEN** HTTP invocation is performed\n351: - **THEN** request SHALL include header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` (uppercase X, capitalized Session, Id)\n352: \n353: #### Scenario: Header response handling\n354: \n355: - **GIVEN** a response contains session header\n356: - **WHEN** the response is processed\n357: - **THEN** the runtime SHALL read `x-agentcube-session-id` (lowercase) from response headers\n358: \n359: ---\n360: \n361: ### Requirement: Error handling for provider operations\n362: \n363: The system SHALL handle Kubernetes API exceptions gracefully.\n364: \n365: #### Scenario: API exception in verbose mode\n366: \n367: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API exception occurs and `verbose=True`\n368: - **WHEN** `_handle_error` is called\n369: - **THEN** CLI SHALL print `Error {command}: {exception}` in red and full traceback, then exit with code `1`\n370: \n371: #### Scenario: Missing Kubernetes dependency\n372: \n373: - **GIVEN** `kubernetes` package is not installed\n374: - **WHEN** provider classes are imported\n375: - **THEN** import SHALL fail or be caught, and CLI SHALL print message suggesting `pip install agentcube[k8s]`\n376: \n377: ---\n378: \n379: ## Implementation Files\n380: \n381: | File | Purpose |\n382: |------|---------|\n383: | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` class |\n384: | `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` class |\n385: | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | `PublishRuntime._publish_k8s`, `_publish_cr_to_k8s` |\n386: | `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | `InvokeRuntime._invoke_agent_via_agentcube`, `_direct_http_invocation` |\n387: | `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | `StatusRuntime._get_k8s_status`, `_get_cr_k8s_status` |\n388: \n389: ---\n390: \n391: ## Dependencies\n392: \n393: | Package | Purpose |\n394: |---------|---------|\n395: | `kubernetes>=28.0.0` | K8s API client, CustomObjectsApi |\n396: | `httpx>=0.24.0` | HTTP client for invocation |\n397: | `pydantic>=2.0.0` | Metadata model |\n398: \n399: ---\n400: \n401: ## Validation Checklist\n402: \n403: - [ ] `KubernetesProvider.__init__` with namespace, kubeconfig, verbose params\n404: - [ ] `KubernetesProvider._ensure_namespace` creates namespace if missing\n405: - [ ] `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` creates Deployment + NodePort Service\n406: - [ ] `KubernetesProvider._sanitize_name` produces DNS-compliant names\n407: - [ ] `KubernetesProvider.wait_for_deployment_ready` polls with timeout\n408: - [ ] `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status` returns running/pending/not_found\n409: - [ ] `KubernetesProvider.delete_agent` removes resources, ignores 404\n410: - [ ] `AgentCubeProvider.__init__` with namespace, kubeconfig, verbose params\n411: - [ ] `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` creates AgentRuntime CR\n412: - [ ] `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime` retrieves CR or returns None\n413: - [ ] `PublishRuntime._publish_k8s` uses KubernetesProvider\n414: - [ ] `PublishRuntime._publish_cr_to_k8s` uses AgentCubeProvider\n415: - [ ] `InvokeRuntime` resolves endpoint based on k8s_deployment.type\n416: - [ ] `StatusRuntime._get_k8s_status` for Deployment type\n417: - [ ] `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` for AgentRuntime type\n418: - [ ] CLI status exits with code 1 for not_published/error\n\n(End of file - total 418 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-026 ŌĆö K8s/AgentCube Provider\n\nAR: AR-026 ŌĆö K8s/AgentCube Provider\nModule: cmd/cli\nLanguage: Python\nSize: M\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement K8s/AgentCube provider integration for deploying AI agents as either standard Kubernetes resources (Deployment + Service) or AgentCube Custom Resources (AgentRuntime CR), enabling lifecycle management through CLI commands.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: KubernetesProvider initialization\n\nThe system SHALL construct `KubernetesProvider` with configurable namespace, kubeconfig path, and verbose logging.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775880632536,"end":1775880632544}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775880632578,"sessionID":"ses_2854548aeffeHHpEDliYv7fzzb","part":{"id":"prt_d7abbf8e2001pwX2J1DL2tfbVc","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7abbe21f001Wx9CgBVGQNMfaH","sessionID":"ses_2854548aeffeHHpEDliYv7fzzb","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":24326,"input":24206,"output":69,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":51}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775880637352,"sessionID":"ses_2854548aeffeHHpEDliYv7fzzb","part":{"id":"prt_d7abc0ba60010nnw3L5kHAJ2Gm","messageID":"msg_d7abbf91d001YU4cuySN1FH5Q1","sessionID":"ses_2854548aeffeHHpEDliYv7fzzb","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880705764,"sessionID":"ses_2854548aeffeHHpEDliYv7fzzb","part":{"id":"prt_d7abd1686001mcwZsCHKdFpA44","messageID":"msg_d7abbf91d001YU4cuySN1FH5Q1","sessionID":"ses_2854548aeffeHHpEDliYv7fzzb","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-21e158c2c8394dbd846f158773b7eb32","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Delta Specification: AR-028 ŌĆö SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n**Module:** sdk-python  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement `AgentRuntimeClient` in the Python SDK for invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router, including session bootstrapping, lifecycle management, and data plane communication.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntimeClient initialization\n\nThe system SHALL construct `AgentRuntimeClient` with configurable agent name, namespace, router URL, session options, and timeout settings.\n\n#### Scenario: Constructor with all parameters\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\", namespace=\"production\", router_url=\"https://router.example.com\", verbose=True, session_id=\"pre-existing-session\", timeout=300, connect_timeout=10.0)`\n- **WHEN** the client is instantiated\n- **THEN** the instance SHALL store `agent_name`, `namespace`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`, `verbose`, `router_url`, and `session_id` as provided\n\n#### Scenario: Default namespace\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\", router_url=\"https://router.example.com\")`\n- **WHEN** the client is instantiated\n- **THEN** `namespace` SHALL default to `\"default\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Router URL from environment\n\n- **GIVEN** environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set to `\"https://router.example.com\"` and `router_url` argument is `None`\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\")` is instantiated\n- **THEN** `router_url` SHALL be read from `os.environ.get(\"ROUTER_URL\")`\n\n#### Scenario: Router URL required\n\n- **GIVEN** neither `router_url` argument nor `ROUTER_URL` environment variable is set\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\")` is instantiated\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with message explaining Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL` environment variable\n\n#### Scenario: Default timeout values\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\", router_url=\"https://router.example.com\")`\n- **WHEN** the client is instantiated\n- **THEN** `timeout` SHALL default to `120` and `connect_timeout` SHALL default to `5.0`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Session ID bootstrapping\n\nThe system SHALL bootstrap `session_id` via `GET` request to the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint when `session_id` is not provided.\n\n#### Scenario: Bootstrap on init when session_id is None\n\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` is `None` during `AgentRuntimeClient` construction\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** it SHALL instantiate `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` and call `bootstrap_session_id()` which performs `GET {router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n\n#### Scenario: Extract session header from bootstrap response\n\n- **GIVEN** the bootstrap `GET` request returns a response\n- **WHEN** the response headers are parsed\n- **THEN** `session_id` SHALL be extracted from header `x-agentcube-session-id`\n\n#### Scenario: Missing session header on bootstrap\n\n- **GIVEN** the bootstrap `GET` request succeeds but response lacks `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n- **WHEN** the client attempts to extract the session ID\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")`\n\n#### Scenario: Reuse provided session_id\n\n- **GIVEN** `session_id=\"existing-session-123\"` is passed to constructor\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** it SHALL NOT call bootstrap and SHALL use the provided `session_id` directly\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Context manager support\n\nThe system SHALL support Python context manager protocol for `AgentRuntimeClient`.\n\n#### Scenario: Enter returns self\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` instance `client`\n- **WHEN** `client.__enter__()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `self`\n\n#### Scenario: Exit closes session\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as `with AgentRuntimeClient(...) as client:`\n- **WHEN** the context block exits (normally or by exception)\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `self.close()`\n\n#### Scenario: Exit suppresses no exceptions\n\n- **GIVEN** an exception occurs inside the context block\n- **WHEN** `__exit__` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `None` (or `False`) to propagate the exception\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Invoke method\n\nThe system SHALL provide `invoke()` method to send JSON payloads to the Agent Runtime.\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke with payload\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` with valid `session_id`\n- **WHEN** `client.invoke({\"input\": \"hello\"})` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL `POST` to `{base_url}` with `json={\"input\": \"hello\"}` and headers `x-agentcube-session-id` and `Content-Type: application/json`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke returns response data\n\n- **GIVEN** `invoke()` receives a successful response with JSON body `{\"result\": \"ok\"}`\n- **WHEN** the response is processed\n- **THEN** `invoke()` SHALL return `response.json()` (the parsed JSON data)\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke without session_id raises\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` with `session_id` set to `None` or empty string\n- **WHEN** `invoke()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke with custom timeout\n\n- **GIVEN** `client.invoke({\"input\": \"test\"}, timeout=30.0)`\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the read timeout SHALL be `30.0` seconds (passed to `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.invoke`)\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke uses default timeout\n\n- **GIVEN** `client.invoke({\"input\": \"test\"})` without `timeout` argument\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the read timeout SHALL be `self.timeout` (default `120`)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient initialization\n\nThe system SHALL construct `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` with router URL, namespace, agent name, and timeout configuration.\n\n#### Scenario: Base URL construction\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"https://router.example.com\", namespace=\"prod\", agent_name=\"my-agent\")`\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** `base_url` SHALL be `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/prod/agent-runtimes/my-agent/invocations/\")`\n\n#### Scenario: Connection pool configuration\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"...\", namespace=\"default\", agent_name=\"agent\", pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=20)`\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** the HTTP session SHALL use `HTTPAdapter` with `pool_connections=20` and `pool_maxsize=20`\n\n#### Scenario: Default pool settings\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is instantiated without pool arguments\n- **WHEN** the HTTP session is created\n- **THEN** `pool_connections` SHALL default to `10` and `pool_maxsize` SHALL default to `10`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Data plane HTTP requests\n\nThe system SHALL make HTTP requests to the Agent Runtime data plane with proper headers and timeout handling.\n\n#### Scenario: Bootstrap GET request\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.bootstrap_session_id()`\n- **WHEN** the request is made\n- **THEN** it SHALL `GET {base_url}` with session default headers only (no `Content-Type`)\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke POST request headers\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.invoke(session_id, payload)`\n- **WHEN** the request is made\n- **THEN** headers SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` and `Content-Type: application/json`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke POST request body\n\n- **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id, {\"action\": \"run\"})`\n- **WHEN** the request is made\n- **THEN** the body SHALL be JSON-serialized payload `{\"action\": \"run\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Timeout tuple format\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` with `connect_timeout=5.0` and `timeout=120`\n- **WHEN** any request is sent\n- **THEN** the `requests` timeout SHALL be `(connect_timeout, timeout)` tuple, i.e., `(5.0, 120)`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke timeout override\n\n- **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id, payload, timeout=60.0)`\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the read timeout component SHALL be `60.0` while connect timeout remains `self.connect_timeout`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Close method\n\nThe system SHALL provide `close()` method to release HTTP resources.\n\n#### Scenario: Close releases session\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` with an active HTTP session\n- **WHEN** `client.close()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `self.dp_client.close()` which closes the underlying `requests.Session`\n\n#### Scenario: Close is idempotent\n\n- **GIVEN** `close()` has already been called on the client\n- **WHEN** `close()` is called again\n- **THEN** it SHALL NOT raise an exception\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Logging\n\nThe system SHALL provide optional verbose logging for debugging.\n\n#### Scenario: Verbose logging disabled by default\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"agent\", router_url=\"...\")`\n- **WHEN** the client is instantiated\n- **THEN** `verbose` SHALL default to `False`\n\n#### Scenario: Logger creation\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is instantiated\n- **WHEN** `__init__` runs\n- **THEN** `self.logger` SHALL be created via `get_logger(__name__)` or similar\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Public API surface\n\nThe system SHALL export `AgentRuntimeClient` from the package root.\n\n#### Scenario: Module export\n\n- **GIVEN** `from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient`\n- **WHEN** the import is executed\n- **THEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` SHALL be available (listed in `agentcube/__init__.py` `__all__`)\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane client not in public API\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is defined in `agentcube.clients.agent_runtime_data_plane`\n- **WHEN** checking `agentcube/__init__.py`\n- **THEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` SHALL NOT be in the root `__all__` (accessible via `agentcube.clients` if needed)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Error handling\n\nThe system SHALL raise appropriate exceptions for error conditions.\n\n#### Scenario: ValueError for missing router_url\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"agent\")` with no `router_url` and no `ROUTER_URL` env var\n- **WHEN** instantiation occurs\n- **THEN** `ValueError` SHALL be raised with message mentioning Router URL requirement\n\n#### Scenario: ValueError for missing session header\n\n- **GIVEN** bootstrap response lacks `x-agentcube-session-id`\n- **WHEN** extracting session ID\n- **THEN** `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")` SHALL be raised\n\n#### Scenario: ValueError for invoke without session\n\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` is `None` or empty\n- **WHEN** `invoke()` is called\n- **THEN** `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")` SHALL be raised\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Header name consistency\n\nThe system SHALL use consistent header names for session identification.\n\n#### Scenario: Session header constant\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class\n- **WHEN** checking class attributes\n- **THEN** `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"` SHALL be defined as a class constant\n\n#### Scenario: Header name lowercase\n\n- **GIVEN** session header is set on requests\n- **WHEN** the header is added\n- **THEN** the header name SHALL be lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id` (not `X-AgentCube-Session-Id`)\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` class |\n| `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class |\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `requests` | HTTP client |\n| `PyJWT>=2.0.0` | JWT handling (if needed) |\n\n---\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` with agent_name, namespace, router_url, verbose, session_id, timeout, connect_timeout\n- [ ] `AgentRuntimeClient` reads `ROUTER_URL` from environment when not provided\n- [ ] `AgentRuntimeClient` raises `ValueError` when router_url is missing\n- [ ] `AgentRuntimeClient` bootstraps session_id via GET request when not provided\n- [ ] `AgentRuntimeClient` extracts `x-agentcube-session-id` header from bootstrap response\n- [ ] `AgentRuntimeClient` raises `ValueError` when session header is missing\n- [ ] `AgentRuntimeClient.__enter__` returns `self`\n- [ ] `AgentRuntimeClient.__exit__` calls `close()`\n- [ ] `AgentRuntimeClient.invoke` POSTs JSON payload with session header\n- [ ] `AgentRuntimeClient.invoke` returns parsed JSON response\n- [ ] `AgentRuntimeClient.invoke` raises `ValueError` when session_id is not initialized\n- [ ] `AgentRuntimeClient.invoke` supports custom timeout\n- [ ] `AgentRuntimeClient.close` closes data plane client\n- [ ] `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` constructs base_url from router_url, namespace, agent_name\n- [ ] `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.bootstrap_session_id` performs GET and returns session_id\n- [ ] `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.invoke` POSTs with correct headers and timeout\n- [ ] `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.SESSION_HEADER` constant is `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n- [ ] `AgentRuntimeClient` exported in `agentcube/__init__.py` `__all__`","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":fals